{"word":"ἀρῐ","slug":"ἀρῐ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n15018\" key=\"a)rĭ\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"pref\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀρῐ-</orth> <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">[ᾰ]</pron>, insep. prefix, <sense id=\"n15018.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">like</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">ἐρι-</ref></xr>, strengthening the notion conveyed by its compd.: cogn. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀρείων, ἄριστος,</foreign> chiefly denoting <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">goodness, excellence</tr_>: mostly in older <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp> and Lyr.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}